Given a matrix of size m x n, write a program to find the maximum element in each row of the matrix.

Input Format

The input consists of (m*n+2) integers.

The first integer corresponds to m, the number of rows in the matrix.

The second integer corresponds to n, the number of columns in the matrix.

The remaining integers correspond to the elements in the matrix. The elements are read in row-wise order (the first row first, then the second row, and so on).

Constraints

NA

Output Format

The output prints the maximum element in each row, each on a new line.

Sample Input 0

3
2
4 5
6 9
0 3
Sample Output 0

5
9
3
Explanation 0

The maximum elements in each row are:

Row 1 → max(4, 5) = 5

Row 2 → max(6, 9) = 9

Row 3 → max(0, 3) = 3



import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int r=sc.nextInt();
       int c=sc.nextInt();
       int arr[][]=new int[r][c];
       for(int i=0;i<r;i++)
       {
        for(int j=0;j<c;j++)
        {
            arr[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
        }
       }
        for(int i=0;i<r;i++)
        {
            int max=0;
            for(int j=0;j<c;j++)
            {
           if(arr[i][j]>max)
           {
            max=arr[i][j];
           } 
            }
            System.out.println(max);
        }
       
    }
}
